 lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Θivy-leafΚ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΙΟΥΛΙΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΓΑΛΗΝΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΗΦΙΛΟΣΤΟΛΟΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΕΖΗΣΕΕΤΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ΛΓ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001302_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo by students of Liceo Lazzaro, courtesy Museo Civico di Catania\" src=\"ISic001302_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001302.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo by students of Liceo Lazzaro, courtesy Museo Civico di Catania\" src=\"ISic001302-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001302_leftthreequarter_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo by students of Liceo Lazzaro, courtesy Museo Civico di Catania\" src=\"ISic001302_leftthreequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001302_leftthreequarter.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo by students of Liceo Lazzaro, courtesy Museo Civico di Catania\" src=\"ISic001302_leftthreequarter-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001302_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo by students of Liceo Lazzaro, courtesy Museo Civico di Catania\" src=\"ISic001302_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001302_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo by students of Liceo Lazzaro, courtesy Museo Civico di Catania\" src=\"ISic001302_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>In the comment Kaibel cautiously suggests to correct φιλόστολος in φιλόστοργος\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To the subterranean deities. Ioulia Galene, 'philostolos', lived for 33 years.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>Agli dèi inferi. Giulia Galene, la φιλόστολος, visse trentatré anni.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph presents the name of the deceased, an epithet and the indication of her age. The reading of the epithet is certain: for this reason, as Kaibel already noticed, there is no need to amend the text. The epithet \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">φιλόστολος\u003C/span> does not seem to be attested elsewhere in Greek texts; it could indicate “the lover of the army or of the fleet (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">στόλος\u003C/span>)” or “the lover of the stola (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">στολή\u003C/span>)”. Rizzone (2009: 202) translates the epithet as “mistress of the fleet”, but already Bertucci (1846: 32) and more recently Korhonen (2004: 213) and Cassia (2020) believe that the epithet refers to \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">στολή\u003C/span> and expresses the status of Ioulia Galene as a freeborn Roman matron. As a matter of fact, the deceased was a Roman citizen, as attested by the nomen \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ἰουλία\u003C/span>. Even though the name Γαλήνη may seem to be a speaking name (“stillness of the sea”) related to the fleet, it seems to have been a female name quite common in the imperial age. Ioulia could have used the epithet as a synonym of the expressions \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">stolata femina\u003C/span> or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ματρῶνα στολάτα\u003C/span> recurring in several inscriptions and papyri, especially from the 2nd-3rd century CE (Cassia 2020: 66-68). The compound would thus be in line with other epithets found in funerary inscriptions and inspired by the family and social virtues of the deceased, such as \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">φιλότεκνος\u003C/span> or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">φίλανδρος\u003C/span>. See also \u003Ca href=\"http://epicum.istc.cnr.it/EPICUM/EpiCUM476\" target=\"_blank\">EpiCum476\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">14.0479\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 99 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Cassia 2020 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002559\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002559\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> Rizzone 2009 202 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001635\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001635\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Bertucci 1846 32 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002303\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002303\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 213 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Cassia 2020 66-68 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002559\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002559\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[245,248,251,254,256,259,262],{"id":246,"html":247},"editions","\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Θ(εοῖς) ivy-leaf Κ(ατακθονίοις) \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Ἰουλία \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Γαλήνη \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ἡ φιλόστολος \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ἔζησε · ἔτη \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">λγ´\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Θivy-leafΚ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΙΟΥΛΙΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΓΑΛΗΝΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΗΦΙΛΟΣΤΟΛΟΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΕΖΗΣΕΕΤΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ΛΓ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":249,"html":250},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>In the comment Kaibel cautiously suggests to correct φιλόστολος in φιλόστοργος\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":252,"html":253},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To the subterranean deities. Ioulia Galene, 'philostolos', lived for 33 years.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":252,"html":255},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>Agli dèi inferi. Giulia Galene, la φιλόστολος, visse trentatré anni.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":257,"html":258},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph presents the name of the deceased, an epithet and the indication of her age. The reading of the epithet is certain: for this reason, as Kaibel already noticed, there is no need to amend the text. The epithet \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">φιλόστολος\u003C/span> does not seem to be attested elsewhere in Greek texts; it could indicate “the lover of the army or of the fleet (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">στόλος\u003C/span>)” or “the lover of the stola (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">στολή\u003C/span>)”. Rizzone (2009: 202) translates the epithet as “mistress of the fleet”, but already Bertucci (1846: 32) and more recently Korhonen (2004: 213) and Cassia (2020) believe that the epithet refers to \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">στολή\u003C/span> and expresses the status of Ioulia Galene as a freeborn Roman matron. As a matter of fact, the deceased was a Roman citizen, as attested by the nomen \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ἰουλία\u003C/span>. Even though the name Γαλήνη may seem to be a speaking name (“stillness of the sea”) related to the fleet, it seems to have been a female name quite common in the imperial age. Ioulia could have used the epithet as a synonym of the expressions \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">stolata femina\u003C/span> or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ματρῶνα στολάτα\u003C/span> recurring in several inscriptions and papyri, especially from the 2nd-3rd century CE (Cassia 2020: 66-68). The compound would thus be in line with other epithets found in funerary inscriptions and inspired by the family and social virtues of the deceased, such as \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">φιλότεκνος\u003C/span> or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">φίλανδρος\u003C/span>. See also \u003Ca href=\"http://epicum.istc.cnr.it/EPICUM/EpiCUM476\" target=\"_blank\">EpiCum476\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":260,"html":261},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">14.0479\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 99 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Cassia 2020 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002559\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002559\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> Rizzone 2009 202 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001635\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001635\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Bertucci 1846 32 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002303\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002303\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 213 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Cassia 2020 66-68 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002559\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002559\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  ",{"id":263,"html":264},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[266,268,271,273,276,278],{"image":130,"thumb":267,"title":133},"ISic001302_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":269,"thumb":270,"title":133},"ISic001302.jpg","ISic001302-thumb.jpg",{"image":136,"thumb":272,"title":133},"ISic001302_leftthreequarter_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":274,"thumb":275,"title":133},"ISic001302_leftthreequarter.jpg","ISic001302_leftthreequarter-thumb.jpg",{"image":140,"thumb":277,"title":133},"ISic001302_rear_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":279,"thumb":280,"title":133},"ISic001302_rear.jpg","ISic001302_rear-thumb.jpg"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
